# 120% Growth From a Channel That Didn't Exist

**How a premium Danish liquorice brand went from zero paid media to 5x+ ROAS — and grew the entire business 120% year on year.**

---

## The Brand

Lakrids by Bülow is Denmark's original gourmet liquorice house. Handcrafted, slow-cooked, unexpected flavour combinations that redefined what liquorice could be. The kind of product that sits in a recycled glass jar on a shelf at a boutique deli and sells itself to anyone who tastes it.

In South Africa, the brand is run by a local distributor who built distribution the traditional way — relationships with retailers, in-store tastings, word of mouth. The product was in the right stores. The brand had a following. But everything happened offline.

## Where They Were

Before Butcherbird, Lakrids had never run a single paid ad. Not one.

Their marketing was email. Their sales were brick and mortar. The Shopify store existed, but it was quiet — a digital storefront with no traffic and no strategy behind it. Online revenue was an afterthought.

It wasn't that the owner didn't want to grow online. She just didn't know where to start. Paid media felt like a different language — CPMs, ROAS, ad sets, creative testing. And the brand had standards. This wasn't a product you could slap a "50% OFF!!!" banner on and push to a cold audience. Everything about Lakrids — the packaging, the ingredients, the presentation — is deliberate and refined. Whatever they did online had to match what the brand felt like in person.

## What We Did

We treated the brand the way it deserved to be treated — like a luxury house, not a DTC startup.

No urgency tactics. No countdown timers. No "Don't miss out!" headlines. Instead, we let the product speak. Short, considered copy. Premium photography. Static ads that looked like they belonged in a magazine, not a Facebook feed.

And it worked immediately.

- A single "Indulge In Luxury" static ad hit **25.39x ROAS** — converting at 43x on its best day before it was even scaled
- Competition and giveaway mechanics became the most consistent converter at **13.06x ROAS**
- Spend-threshold offers during gifting season drove **45.23x ROAS** at R109 per purchase

We didn't just run ads. We built an entire online revenue channel from nothing — the strategy, the creative, the funnel, the testing framework. Everything.

## What Happened

- **120% total business growth** year on year — not just online, the entire business
- A **45.23x ROAS** campaign that turned R1 into R45
- An online revenue channel built from zero — now a core part of the business

That last number isn't a typo. When the creative matches the brand and the offer matches the audience, those are the numbers that are possible.

## The Bigger Picture

What made Lakrids special wasn't just the ROAS. It was the proof that paid media doesn't have to cheapen a premium brand.

The owner had held off on advertising because she was afraid it would dilute what made Lakrids special. Instead, it amplified it. The same elegance, the same craftsmanship story, the same quiet confidence — just in front of thousands more people.

Online sales didn't just add a new revenue stream. They drove people into retail stores. They built brand awareness that made every other channel stronger. The 120% year-on-year growth wasn't just an online number — it was the whole business.

Sometimes the product is already perfect. It just needs the right people to see it.

---

**Headline stat:** 120% YoY growth